A 9-year-old girl was injured when she was tossed in the air by a bison at the Yellowstone National Park in the United States of America. Officials of the park have confirmed that a bull bison tossed the 9-year-old girl into the air on Monday when the animal charged at a group of comprising some 50 tourists. The girl whose identity is being protected is said to have since been released from the hospital. Photo via @abc4utah.